    "(2) In general, we say that the Mordell-Weil group A(K) over a field",
    "and A(k g,m) are known to have infinite rank.",
    "For example, this is the case for both A(K g,m) and A(k g,m) if A is the Jacobian variety of a hyperelliptic curve of genus ≤ g defined over k and m p ≥ 1 for infinitely many p (cf.",
